Version 0.25.1 Info
July 29, 2012
Released under GNU General Public License, version 3.0 About this Add-on
ImageTweak started as a small enhancement to allow viewing images in an acceptable way, but has now become an image viewer with dragging and zooming.Right-click (or arrow keys) to scroll, ctrl+scroll the mouse wheel (or +/-) to zoom, double-right-click (or space-bar) to cycle through full-view, 1:1-view and free-view.Looking for help using ImageTweak? Read the ImageTweak user guide.Found a bug? Want to suggest a feature? Go to the bugs and feature request page.Please do not submit bug reports or feature requests in the review section (below). I don't receive any notification about reviews, so I may not even notice your message.The source code of ImageTweak is available on GitHub. You can contribute by sending pull requests and patches. You can also contribute to the development of ImageTweak by sending bitcoins to 1265ciMoFwnX4y4gGxXNGkiD7Qu24oYSqw or by donating via Paypal.
Developer’s Comments
BUG REPORTS IN THE REVIEWS WILL BE IGNORED: TO REPORT A BUG GO TO >>THIS PAGE<<
